========================================================
Run parameters for the anasum stage
========================================================

========================================================
All lines without a '*' in the first column are ignored!
--------------------------------------------------------

Time mask
---------

File containing time mask details 
(this allows to exclude certain time intervals from 
the analysis)
 TIMEMASKFILE <file name of time mask file>
* TIMEMASKFILE ANASUM.timemask.dat

Exclusion regions
-----------------

Exclusion region around sky map centre
(should be adjust to brightness of the gamma-ray source
and the cuts applied)
 REGIONTOEXCLUDE <x-derot [deg]> <y-derot [deg]> <radius of exlusion region [deg]>
* REGIONTOEXCLUDE 0. 0. 0.35

User defined regions in the sky to exclude from background 
estimation (e.g. because of other gamma-ray sources in the
field of view

Exclusion region can be 

1. circles
If Radius1=Radius2 (or if no Radius2 is given) and theta=0

2. ellipses
If Radius1!=Radius2

3. rotated ellipses
If Radius1!=Radius2 and theta!=0

->REGIONTOEXCLUDE (West(deg)  North(deg)  Radius(deg))
(coordinates are relative to camera center)
ex: 0.48 -0.2 0.5
Note: West positive means toward West (left in camera coordinates)
North positive means toward South (up in camera coordinates)
->REGIONTOEXCLUDE_RADECJ2000_DEG (RA(deg) DEC(deg) Radius(deg))
ex: 335.287 58.964 0.5
->REGIONTOEXCLUDE_RADECJ2000_HOUR (RA(Hour Min Sec)  DEC(Deg Min Sec)  Radius(deg))
ex:12 24 15 52 18 04 0.5

->REGIONTOEXCLUDE (West(deg)  North(deg)  Radius1(deg) Radius2(deg) theta(deg))
(coordinates are relative to camera center)
ex: 0.48 -0.2 0.5 0.5 40
Note: West positive means toward West (left in camera coordinates)
North positive means toward South (up in camera coordinates)
->REGIONTOEXCLUDE_RADECJ2000_DEG (RA(deg) DEC(deg) Radius1(deg) Radius2(deg) theta(deg))
ex: 335.287 58.964 0.5 0.5 40
->REGIONTOEXCLUDE_RADECJ2000_HOUR (RA(Hour Min Sec)  DEC(Deg Min Sec)  Radius1(deg) Radius2(deg) theta(deg))
ex:12 24 15 52 18 04 0.5 0.5 40

